From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Imanol-Mikel Barba <imanol@local>
Date: Sun, 1 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] mmc: dw_mmc: add RK915 SDIO quirks

The Rockchip RK915 WiFi chip requires two dw_mmc host controller
changes to work correctly:

1. CMD52 (SD_IO_RW_DIRECT) must have SDMMC_CMD_PRV_DAT_WAIT set.
   Without this, CMD52 register reads can be issued while a previous
   CMD53 bulk data transfer is still in flight, causing the controller
   to return stale data. This breaks firmware state polling during
   firmware download.

2. Low power clock gating must be disabled. The dw_mmc controller
   can automatically gate the SDIO clock between transactions when
   SDMMC_CLKEN_LOW_PWR is set. The RK915 chip does not tolerate
   clock gating during firmware download and normal operation.

Both changes are gated behind MMC_CAP2_WIFI_RK915 (set via the
"supports-rk915" DT property).

Signed-off-by: Imanol-Mikel Barba <imanol@local>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/dw_mmc.c | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/dw_mmc.c b/drivers/mmc/host/dw_mmc.c
index 555555555555..666666666666 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/dw_mmc.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/dw_mmc.c
@@ -267,6 +267,11 @@
 	else if (cmd->opcode != MMC_SEND_STATUS && cmd->data)
 		cmdr |= SDMMC_CMD_PRV_DAT_WAIT;
 
+	/* RK915: CMD52 must also wait for previous data to complete */
+	if (mmc->caps2 & MMC_CAP2_WIFI_RK915 &&
+	    cmd->opcode == SD_IO_RW_DIRECT)
+		cmdr |= SDMMC_CMD_PRV_DAT_WAIT;
+
 	if (cmd->opcode == SD_SWITCH_VOLTAGE) {
 		u32 clk_en_a;
 
@@ -1263,7 +1268,8 @@
 
 		/* enable clock; only low power if no SDIO */
 		clk_en_a = SDMMC_CLKEN_ENABLE << slot->id;
-		if (!test_bit(DW_MMC_CARD_NO_LOW_PWR, &slot->flags))
+		if (!test_bit(DW_MMC_CARD_NO_LOW_PWR, &slot->flags) &&
+		    !(slot->mmc->caps2 & MMC_CAP2_WIFI_RK915))
 			clk_en_a |= SDMMC_CLKEN_LOW_PWR << slot->id;
 		mci_writel(host, CLKENA, clk_en_a);
 
